@@ -219,31 +219,40 @@
 - Tool calls that can mutate external resources run through a resource lease wrapper. If another turn is already working on the same namespace/resource, the later turn is blocked or redirected instead of issuing contradictory API calls.
 - Scheduled and proactive outbound sends use idempotency keys and retry/backoff state.
 - The Telegram UX no longer sends generic placeholder messages. The bot uses chat-action typing and only opens/edits a live message once real assistant text exists.
-- A runtime controller chooses fast/smart/reasoning models, reasoning effort, streaming behavior, and tool-step budget from message/context metrics plus a small model router. It does not route by fixed keyword/intent lists.
+- A latency-first runtime controller chooses fast/smart/reasoning models, reasoning effort, streaming behavior, and tool-step budget from message/context metrics. It does not route by fixed keyword/intent lists; the optional model-router hop is disabled unless `AGENT_DYNAMIC_REASONING=model`.
 - Durable memory records recent turn events, user facts, session summaries, and checkpointed work items in Redis.
 
 ### Runtime env knobs
 
 ```bash
 # Dynamic effort/model selection
-AGENT_DYNAMIC_REASONING=true
+AGENT_DYNAMIC_REASONING=local
 FAST_MODEL_NAME=gpt-4o-mini
 SMART_MODEL_NAME=gpt-4o
 # Set REASONING_MODEL_NAME to a reasoning-capable model to enable effort routing.
 REASONING_MODEL_NAME=
+# Set AGENT_DYNAMIC_REASONING=model to enable the extra model-router hop.
 ROUTER_MODEL_NAME=gpt-4o-mini
 INTAKE_MODEL_NAME=gpt-4o-mini
 MEMORY_MODEL_NAME=gpt-4o-mini
+AGENT_FAST_PATH_TOOLS=true
+AGENT_EAGER_TOOLS=false
+COMPOSIO_EAGER_TOOLS=false
 
 # Human-feeling delivery
 TELEGRAM_STREAMING=true
 TELEGRAM_TYPING_INTERVAL_MS=4000
 TELEGRAM_STREAM_CHUNK_CHARS=3500
+TELEGRAM_STREAM_FIRST_CHARS=24
+TELEGRAM_EDIT_THROTTLE_MS=220
 
 # Queue/coalescing/fault tolerance
 INBOUND_DEDUPE_TTL_SECONDS=1209600
 INBOUND_PROCESSING_LEASE_MS=600000
-MESSAGE_COHERENCE_WINDOW_MS=2200
+MESSAGE_COHERENCE_WINDOW_MS=700
+MESSAGE_COHERENCE_LONG_WINDOW_MS=2200
+SESSION_QUEUE_POLL_MS=250
+INTAKE_USE_MODEL=false
 SPLIT_MESSAGE_JOIN_WINDOW_MS=4500
 SESSION_MAX_MESSAGES_PER_BATCH=12
 SESSION_PROCESSOR_LOCK_SECONDS=900
